    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Out-of-Bounds Access in PRS Generation Loop\n\n### Summary\nThe PRS (Positioning Reference Signal) generation function `nr_generate_prs` in the gNB PHY layer contains a potential out-of-bounds array access when handling large PRS configurations. Under certain conditions where the number of PRS resource blocks is at maximum (272 RBs) and the comb size is minimal (2), the inner loop index `m` can exceed the bounds of both the `mod_prs` buffer and the `gold` sequence array.\n\nSpecifically, when `m` reaches 1632, the code attempts to access `gold[m >> 4]` which evaluates to `gold[102]`, but the `gold` array is only allocated with 102 elements (indices 0-101). This leads to undefined behavior and potential crashes during PRS transmission.\n\nThe fix introduces a bounds check on the loop limit to ensure `m` never exceeds 1631, preventing the out-of-bounds access while maintaining correct PRS generation for all valid configurations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_TRANSPORT/nr_prs.c`: Added bounds checking for the PRS generation loop index to prevent accessing beyond the `gold` sequence array limits. Also fixed a debug log line referencing an incorrect variable name.\n"
}